        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is NAV in stocks?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "NAV stands for Net Asset Value. It is the total value of a fund's assets minus its liabilities, divided by the number of shares outstanding. It represents the true per-share value of a mutual fund or ETF."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How often is NAV calculated?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "For mutual funds, NAV is calculated once a day at the close of the market. For ETFs, an indicative NAV (iNAV) is calculated every 15 seconds during trading hours, with a final official NAV at the close."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can a stock have a NAV?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
